<exercise checkit-seed="0003" checkit-slug="DiffQuotient" checkit-title="Difference Quotient">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Suppose that there is a function <m>g</m> such that <m>g(0) = 3.4</m> and <m>g(-0.1) = 2.8</m>. Use these values to estimate <m>g'(0)</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>
            g'(0) \approx \frac{ g(-0.1) - g(0) }{ (-0.1) - (0) } = 
            \frac{ (2.8) - (3.4) }{ (-0.1) - (0) } = 6.00
        </me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
